============================================================

Written the improvement plan. Here's the summary:

**Two fixes for two failures:**

1. **"Baked Eggs... → ''"** — The sole valid candidate passes all hard filters but embeddings can't distinguish "dish named after its ingredients" from "ingredient list fragment". Fix: **empty-pool fallback** — when threshold filtering discards every candidate, return the best positional one. Hard filters already exclude real noise; embeddings shouldn't have absolute veto.

2. **"Faszerowana papryka → PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM"** — The first-line protection is self-defeating: it requires the mixed-case title to survive threshold, but the ALL_CAPS bonuses inflate the threshold beyond its reach. Fix: **pre-threshold bilingual detection** — detect the pattern on the full `scored` array and suppress the ALL_CAPS subtitle *before* computing threshold. Then remove the old post-threshold guard (lines 468-479).

The fixes are independent, non-overlapping, and neither can fire on currently-passing tests (fix 1 only triggers when `selected` is empty; fix 2 only triggers with exactly 1 ALL_CAPS at pos ≤ 2 behind a mixed-case pos-0).
