{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Sny9GaCHb5uRoq7QGdsrYD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the problem. Let me also look at the test inputs to understand the data better.\n\nLet me think about the two failures:\n\n**Failure 1: \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\" → ''**\n- The merged candidate passes all hard filters but gets killed by embedding scoring because ingredient-like words pull it toward HEADER_REFERENCE\n- Root cause: embedding-based scoring penalizes ingredient-heavy titles, and there's no fallback for single-candidate pools\n\n**Failure 2: \"Faszerowana papryka\" → 'PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM'**\n\n\n- The first-line protection needs both candidates in `selected`, but the mixed-case Polish title gets filtered out by the threshold since ALL_CAPS bonuses inflate the score\n- Root cause: the protection happens after thresholding, so it can't help when one candidate is already eliminated\n\nFor solutions, I should add a fallback when only one candidate survives the hard filters—if it passes all the strict requirements, it shouldn't be discarded by the embedding score alone. I also need to move the first-line protection earlier in the pipeline, before the threshold eliminates candidates that could otherwise be protected.\n\nThe cleanest approach is a position-0 safety net: if the top candidate passes hard filters but falls below threshold, force it into the selected pool anyway. This prevents the ALL_CAPS bonus inflation from eliminating unambiguous matches.\n\nI should also add a fallback for when all candidates miss the threshold—just return the highest-scoring one that passed hard filters, preferring position 0. The hard filters already screen for garbled text and metadata issues, so this shouldn't introduce noise.\n\nLet me work through the implementation details.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":56,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1232,"cache_read_input_tokens":31472,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1232},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7bdf839d-85df-40e4-96e0-3a9dda0250b7","uuid":"c691de07-7654-4391-a1fe-3bc750a5b3f8"}
