{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01R2Lm37xnf7DW1SEUBStzda","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have full context. Here's my analysis of the two failures and proposed fixes:\n\n---\n\n**Failure 1 (\"Baked Eggs... → ''\"):** The merged candidate passes all hard filters but embedding scoring kills it because ingredient words (Feta, Harissa, Coriander) pull it toward `HEADER_REFERENCE`. With `rawScore ≤ 0`, it falls below threshold and `selected` becomes empty. **Fix:** Add an empty-pool fallback — if all candidates are below threshold but at least one passed hard filters, return the best positional candidate rather than nothing. The hard filters already exclude real noise; embeddings shouldn't have absolute veto power over the only surviving candidate.\n\n**Failure 2 (\"Faszerowana papryka → PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\"):** The first-line protection (lines 468-479) is dead code for the case it was designed for. It checks `selected` after threshold filtering, but the ALL_CAPS bonuses inflate the threshold beyond what the mixed-case Polish title can reach. **Fix:** Run the bilingual detection on the full `scored` array *before* threshold filtering. When a mixed-case pos-0 candidate is followed by a single ALL_CAPS line at pos ≤ 2, force-include the pos-0 candidate in `selected` and suppress the ALL_CAPS candidate — regardless of their scores.\n\nLet me write the improvement plan."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1486,"cache_read_input_tokens":33966,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1486},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7bdf839d-85df-40e4-96e0-3a9dda0250b7","uuid":"18129141-622c-4344-92b3-8777cff56911"}
