{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01E6xKcL3UhWnwi1tYTAjgzQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Written the improvement plan. Here's the summary:\n\n**Two fixes for two failures:**\n\n1. **\"Baked Eggs... → ''\"** — The sole valid candidate passes all hard filters but embeddings can't distinguish \"dish named after its ingredients\" from \"ingredient list fragment\". Fix: **empty-pool fallback** — when threshold filtering discards every candidate, return the best positional one. Hard filters already exclude real noise; embeddings shouldn't have absolute veto.\n\n2. **\"Faszerowana papryka → PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\"** — The first-line protection is self-defeating: it requires the mixed-case title to survive threshold, but the ALL_CAPS bonuses inflate the threshold beyond its reach. Fix: **pre-threshold bilingual detection** — detect the pattern on the full `scored` array and suppress the ALL_CAPS subtitle *before* computing threshold. Then remove the old post-threshold guard (lines 468-479).\n\nThe fixes are independent, non-overlapping, and neither can fire on currently-passing tests (fix 1 only triggers when `selected` is empty; fix 2 only triggers with exactly 1 ALL_CAPS at pos ≤ 2 behind a mixed-case pos-0)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4766,"cache_read_input_tokens":35452,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4766},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7bdf839d-85df-40e4-96e0-3a9dda0250b7","uuid":"cacc7762-1fbd-4c0f-8169-bf1df83c361c"}
